result.name: Tsui Wah

reviews.text: I ordered 2 dishes and a drink to go. I had to wait over 40 minutes while I watched over 15 various dishes be served to other "to go" orders and customers who entered and sat down AFTER I had placed my order. One of the workers had seen me waiting, went for a break, came back, and muttered quietly "why has he been waiting there so long?" I'm perfectly fine with waiting for food but when there's no mention of why an order takes so long and all kinds of dishes are being prioritized significantly, it's quite unacceptable. No apologies were given, and no explanations were given when asked.
Food quality is consistent, but the number of staffs are really not enough, hard to get a waiter to take orders

I came here with my parents to grab some breakfast and I'd definitely recommend coming here. The food is relatively cheap and worth your every single dollar. Compared to HK cafes in Los Angeles, this spot is so much cheaper and more filling compared to the ones I've had. My favorite was their pineapple bread, especially when it's fresh out of the oven.
Quality food. And the service is highly efficient, very high table turn over rate.
Very traditional TASTES of HK from 1960s to 80s

result.name: Shatin Plaza

reviews.text: Standard shipping mall with more of a focus on lower-cost staples than the luxury segment. Connected to the other Sha Tin masks through walkways - don't expect to cross the street easily - but nothing much noteworthy here beyond that. Good food a quick visit if you are around and need something, unlikely to warrant a trip for its own sake.
An oldish mall. But busy . Seem to be good place for pharmaceutical n cosmetics products.
Good shopping plaza , a lot of famous brand shops . If u want to buy cheap , still got shops under hkd100. Enjoy

Alright shopping centre.

The first ever time I came here it was when I was really young and they used to have a water fountain (yes that was a very long time ago!).

It is a shame they don't have a centre piece anymore and so the shopping centre lacks that edge which differentiates it from other shopping centres.
Very accessible and connected to adjacent shopping malls.

商場內有不少店舖：
上層有：
食店有：大快活、太興燒味、翠華餐廳、
麵包店有：東海堂、聖安娜、
中西藥品有：余仁生、位元堂、北京同仁堂、萬寧、屈臣氏、華潤堂、裕華保健坊、數間中西藥房、維特健靈專門店，
老鳳祥銀樓、榮華、雞仔嘜、 鱷魚恤、Bossini、Wanko、CAMELA、GIORDANO、Rainbow，
流動電訊服務：電訊數碼，3香港，中國移動，CSL，有線寬頻，電訊數碼等等
有眼鏡88、時間廊、Bossini 、佐丹奴
地下有數間銀行：分別是滙豐銀行、揸打銀行、中國銀行、星展銀行、東亞銀行，花旗銀行等等、惠康超級市場、佳寶食品。基本上還是能夠滿足顧客的需要，行人通道比較窄，人多的時候要注意，是不錯的購物點。
沙田廣場飲食雲集，名牌商店齊全，交通方便，是消費者勝地。
乜都唔錯, 就係太多藥房同大陸人..大陸人坐晒係地下....*_*
